Different person here but I personally tried this ^^ and for some reason it didn’t work for me. It’s definitely worth a shot though! It might depend on the other department? What I ended up doing was contacting an adviser in the non-EECS course’s department and explaining the situation to her and she was able to manually enroll me in the class

Hi, I realize that EECS classes are now set to allow time conflicts with other classes, but I wonder if anyone knows what happens if this conflict is with a class from another department (one which does not automatically allows conflicts)?

  1. Would I be able to enroll in both classes?
  2. Does the order in which I enroll matter? (i.e. should I enroll in the CS class first or second

Thanks!
